.TH CCM 1 "April 2026" "ccm" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ccm \- Claude Credentials Manager \(em manage multiple Claude OAuth sessions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ccm
.I command
.RI [ arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ccm
is a command-line tool for managing multiple Claude Code OAuth credentials.
It allows you to authenticate multiple Claude accounts, switch between them,
and manage their lifecycle (refresh, rename, remove).
.PP
Credentials are stored locally in
.B ~/.ccm/
as individual JSON files with permission 0600. When a credential is activated,
.B ccm
creates a symlink (or file copy on Windows) from
.B ~/.claude/.credentials.json
to
.BR ~/.claude/ccm.credentials.json ,
allowing Claude Code to use the selected account.
.PP
The original
.B ~/.claude/.credentials.json
is backed up to
.B ~/.claude/bk.credentials.json
on first activation and can be restored at any time.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B login
Authenticate a new Claude account via OAuth (PKCE flow). Opens the browser
for authorization; the user pastes the authorization code back into the terminal.
A new credential is created with a UUID identifier.
.TP
.BI "use " id-or-name
Activate a credential for Claude Code. Writes the selected credential to
.B ~/.claude/ccm.credentials.json
and symlinks
.B ~/.claude/.credentials.json
to it. If the token is expired, prompts to refresh before activation.
.TP
.B status
List all credentials in a table showing: ID (8-char prefix), name,
status (valid/expired), expiry time, usage quota, and an active marker (*).
.TP
.BI "refresh " id-or-name
Refresh the OAuth token for a credential. If the credential is currently
active, the active credential file is also updated.
.TP
.BI "logout " id-or-name
Remove a credential. If the credential is currently active, prompts for
confirmation unless
.B \-f
or
.B \-\-force
is specified.
.TP
.BI "rename " "id-or-name new-name"
Assign a friendly name to a credential.
.I new-name
must be 1\(en32 characters consisting of alphanumeric characters, hyphens,
or underscores. Names must be unique across all credentials.
.TP
.B restore
Undo
.BR "ccm use" :
remove the symlink (or managed copy) and restore the original
.B ~/.claude/.credentials.json
from backup.
.SH CREDENTIAL RESOLUTION
All commands accepting
.I id-or-name
resolve the argument in the following order:
.TP 4
1.
Exact UUID match
.TP 4
2.
Exact name match
.TP 4
3.
UUID prefix match (minimum 4 characters). If the prefix is ambiguous
(matches multiple credentials), an error is returned listing all matches.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
(logout only) Skip confirmation when removing an active credential.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help for any command.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.ccm/
Credential storage directory. Each credential is stored as
.IR <uuid> .credentials.json
with permission 0600.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/.credentials.json
Claude Code credential file. Managed by
.B ccm
as a symlink (Unix) or copy (Windows) when a credential is active.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/ccm.credentials.json
Active credential written by
.BR ccm .
The symlink target on Unix systems.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/bk.credentials.json
Backup of the original credential file, created on first
.B ccm use
invocation. Never overwritten if it already exists.
.SH EXAMPLES
Authenticate a new account:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ccm login
.fi
.RE
.PP
Give the credential a friendly name:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ccm rename a1b2c3d4 work
.fi
.RE
.PP
Switch to the "work" credential:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ccm use work
.fi
.RE
.PP
View all credentials and their status:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ccm status
.fi
.RE
.PP
Refresh an expired token:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ccm refresh work
.fi
.RE
.PP
Restore original credentials:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ ccm restore
.fi
.RE
.SH PLATFORM NOTES
On Unix and macOS, credential switching uses symbolic links. On Windows,
file copies are used instead, with a
.B ccmSourceId
marker in the JSON to track the active credential.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred.
